  pdf = {../../FTPDIR/monotone_near_monotone_sontag_systems_synthetic_biology_2007.pdf},
abstract = {
This paper provides an expository introduction to monotone and
near-monotone biochemical network structures.
Monotone systems respond in a predictable fashion to perturbations, and have
very robust dynamical characteristics.
This makes them reliable components of more complex networks, and suggests
that natural biological systems may have evolved to be, if not monotone, at
least close to monotone.
In addition, interconnections of monotone systems may be fruitfully analyzed
using tools from control theory.
