pdf = {../../FTPDIR/malisoff_sontag_lsu_springer2004.pdf},
abstract = {
We discuss several issues related to the stabilizability of nonlinear systems.
First, for continuously stabilizable systems, we review constructions of
feedbacks that render the system input-to-state stable with respect to
actuator errors.  Then, we discuss a recent paper which
provides a new feedback design that makes globally asymptotically controllable
