nonsingular control sequences. A particular application is given
by considering forward accessible systems on compact manifolds.
For general systems, it is proved that the complement of the set of
universal sequences of infinite length is of the first category.
For classes of systems satisfying a descending chain
condition, and in particular for systems defined by polynomial dynamics,
forward accessibility implies uniform forward accessibility.
},
}

